description:
Clickable areas in the application (especially table rows in the object detail Dictionary and Migration views) did not visually indicate that they were interactive. Adding a `.clickable` CSS class with `cursor: pointer` provides clear affordance.

### CSS Added
```css
.clickable {
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

The entire row was made clickable — hovering over any cell in the row shows the pointer cursor, and clicking selects the row.
